content: Good game, takes some learning but fun. Leveling is way too hard and controls need just a little help. I played the whole thing and enjoyed it, but barely reached level 6.

Nice and simple design as it should be for small mobile games, very enjoyable until you finish the limited amount of maps. Random map could have more options, researchable unlimited passive resource generation, orbital defenses and among other things are desired.

I keep coming back to this game, honestly the most satisfying mobile game I've played. Simple strategy, well thought out. I would love a second version. More races? More maps? Blueplop are talented with game design, even tho this is simple. I put this up with AOE and C&C
Good level of complexity and strategic options. Just wish there was more campaign.
Super simple but fun mobile game that still works offline. Sadly doesn't support the full screen of my Galaxy s10, instead it has huge black bars at the top and bottom of the screen
Such a fun game to play.
-A build/conquer real-time strategy game. -100% functional offline. -the Best of Bluplop
when will you provide update? this game is promising
Great simple but addictive
Fun gameplay, with easy to use interface.
This game has been installed in my 4th phone since I bought it back in 2012. Random maps are good.
Would love some more scenarios.
My main issue was game won't play on SD Card, otherwise a good game.
I am at level 22. Do not have any problems. Excellent value for 1.54USD. However, need some updates , such as Huge map more start up upgradeS. Pls consider.
I can't call menu to turn off sound.
Great value. Have spent many hours on this.
Great time killer.
It took me a while to get passed the tutorial levels. I like a game that isn't too easy to pass each level.

It's a fast paced strategy game, I play a random map with my morning coffee to get my mind working.  I beat it pretty fast, I think it's fairly easy.  I'd love to see more maps, campaigns, muliti player, larger maps, etc.  I've purchased all of their games, but this is the best.  I hope they consider adding to it.  I would pay more for more content.
Needs a build ship button

Sadly I purchased the game hoping to see a lot more campaigns and maps hopefully regular updates. Sadly that wasn't happening. I have downloaded third party maps and campaigns, yet I am not able to see them though I have  copied the files to respective folders. Please help me
I tried to load Gary's maps from SD and game crashed. Lost all info. Have to start over. Probably won't.

There's some potential here, it just feels rushed/unpolished. I'd happily pay more if they released an extended or advanced version.  As it stands,  I just feel this is lacking and I'm uninstalling the day after I bought it (I got through most of the game before getting bored).
Well, that was fun, but I expected a bit more challenge.  How do I make my own maps?
I'd love to see a multiplayer mode!
Good game
Please ton down the enemy ai. I seriously die with in the first 10 minutes.
So much fun
fun and challenging, worth the money

Very pleased, just wish the universe was larger.  Ends too quick.  Would like to see additional races with different abilities to keep it interesting.   Perhaps some space monsters or random events.   One of my top 3 games.  Was no. 1 for a long time, but now getting a little old for reasons stated.
I love this app. One of the best in my opinion. I made a map and saved it directly to the folder where it should go to be playable but the app hasn't allowed me to even see it on SD card menu.

Love the game, I paid and was not disappointed. Great app, simple to play, very satisfying challenge. But I've mastered the random maps already. Its been 3days. Three computers at the hardest setting. Hope the Star Colonies team reads this. I suggest a galaxy map, what i mean is a map that is alot larger, more computers, harder also, special events to happen in this Galaxy. Mabey a closed system multiplayer. I would pay good money to play that game...like I mean a **** load of money  Xp    Keep on making!
Not breath taking but enterteined.

This is a solid game and it could use a lot more content.  The only thing keeping this from a 5 star rating is the lack of auto save.  If you are seconds from winning a game and you take a phone call, when you return you will be greeted by the start menu.  Would also like the ability to clear the campaign flags so you could go through them as if brand new (currently you have to remember which scenario you just played, and then pick the next one as opposed to just grabbing the highest scenario available)
There aren't enough Campaigns in the paid version. Still entertaining though.
Update fixed the white screen issue. Awesome!
replyContent:
Hello, 

we are very sorry for the problems, but the "white creen" should be fixed in current update (1.2.16).

BluePlop team

content: Needs a guide!
Can't play since update on my nexus 7. I paid for the full version. Please fix or in update till you have it working.
Long ago beat all the scenarios, but still enjoy a random map now and then.  We'll worth it for the full version.
Fun tech trees

What i thought would be a good time waster, turned into a waste of time.  By the time you have researched a minimal amount of upgrades your opposition have taken over the galaxy...move along people don't waste your time or money  on this travesty of a so called game

Excellent graphics. This game has been really well done. The hard levels are hard. Nice use of icons beside each star. Games take minutes to hours to complete in self contained missions. Would love to have an expansion on this game. Recommend to sci fi rts gamers.
Some of the campaigns are challenging. Simple yet fun.

Blue pop makes awesome games. Love all of them, except it looks like it's heading the way of in-app purchases... The absolute worst way to keep loyal customers in my opinion. I avoid in-app purchase games like the plague
Great strategy game that will keep you entertained for hours !   Keep up the good work Blue Plop:-)
Its pretty basic I wish the graphics were a little bit more but its pretty good overall it needs a lot more in depth material though
level 6  in training is impossible to beat
Well balanced and fun
Addictive strategy
Maybe my expectations were off. The mechanics of the game were a turn off for me. Not a fan of game that make you put your units into a meat grinder.
Wish it had more levels.
Purchased, played, loved it, uninstalled. Months later went to reinstall and unable to do so?
Great stratagy game
Great game.  I have a samsung s4 and had no problems with this game.
A nice, simple clone of Imperium Galactica 2.
Hard to win!!!
Finished all scenarios weeks ago.  Any updates coming?
Very difficult but achievable strategy game. Recommended.
Full version installed. SD card button disappears after dropping maps in the folder.
It took me a couple of weeks before I could beat every scenario, so it is well worth buying the full version for the time you'll be spending on it.

Strategy game on ANDROID I ever played. I finish all the campain+ custom maps. I'm a bit disapointed that after u upgrade at maximum and you make more levels you get nothing extra. But is way,way better than most strategy games for phone and tablets. Btw I wait for next version and put one programmer to make a couple more custom maps or why not more campaigns :)... Great game! Bravo
Needs some work its glichy
Great game, really really tough but not impossible.  Could do with a few different fighter types but all in all a fine rts
Fun, challenging.

Reminder of classic era of PC games, return to the concept proofed true long time ago. Gets a little repetitive after you learn the mechanics; varied mission design tries to compensate, with some success.
This is a really good game, although the AI is a little hard and i would of liked to see more lab tech upgrades
Easy to learn and best   once I learn the build order it's easy.   Fun go plonk around with
A good solid game, but I feel that one more race and a few more technologies would only improve the game.

Could do with some optional complexity - maybe an expansion? As it is its great but a shade too simple - could do with more econ or more ship types or more structures or... something.   Nevertheless is really fun - put in the effort to figure out how to play and you'll have a good time.
Plays fine g2x
I find this game actually challenges me and keeps me playing instead of getting bored and quitting.
Wish list: Spying (Espionage and Sabotage) Space tactical combat Ground combat Make treaties like alliances Facial expression from foreign ambassadors
Enjoying immensely, still getting use to gameplay. The game is complicated, but enjoying learning as I go. I will send more notes to the author as I advance. Thank you for a fine effort!

Doesn't matter how high you level, you can't have enough initial power /technology to defeat multiple opponents in hard..  "normal" mode is almost impossible with three opponents.  Still..  Fun game..
A simple but fun game.  AI is a bit dumb on random maps, but there's still a score challenge.  Only game I've ever purchased, glad I did.
Superb
Wish there was more.

Fun, simple time-killer but in very desperate need of additional maps and features. The AI is weak and predictable. Add different ships, options, races and technology types and it might get interesting. Otherwise, it's very limited.
In some of the campaign levels, I can't reach the next solar system. Even though I have well over twice the required distance to get there...
Great game. Lots of fun!
Simple yet fun
Seriously addictive. Simple enough to play on a phone but complex enough to keep me entertained for weeks.
A fair effort but very boring game. No strategy needed, just mine resources and repeat. Also no icon explanations and poor control layout. Plenty of similar and better free games available
Good game

I have it on 2 devices but saved progress isn't synced together. Also when you gain experience you dont get better from the start to give you one up on opponent, it just allows you to gain high level in the game. I would think leveling up would give u a free technology from the start. Like the first block of attack is already fulled in from the start. You know?
Halfway through second tutorial mission and I knew I had to buy it.  Fans of MOO .... get this!
Smooth, fun, engaging without being too complicated, this game is a brilliant example of what strategy games on mobile devices should be! Love it!
Absolutly love the game the only thing it needs is another type of fighter or vessel. Keep up the great work!!!!
It's hard at beginning, enjoy after all. Simple graphics, but more strategy to win. Update More scenario please!
Great game, just wish I could play in portrait mode

Love the game, I enjoy the different tactics associated with each race!  Few things to point out, the game runs a cumaltive effect on buildings but you dont have a tutorial or faq that states this. I had to test the theory out after wondering why the AI was doping it.

You should move the mute option to under an option menu in the game, rather than the drop menu for smartphones. My tablet (Samsung galaxy note) since the update doesn't play any sound affects but the music still plays. Same goes for my s3 but I can fix it on my s3 by turning sound off and on in app. Its still a great game regardless of that bug.
Great little real-time strategy title. Thank you for not offering ingame purchases!

I like this game a lot, because I like land management games.  It is good because it only has a few elements, but those elements may be combined into extremely complicated maps.  I've even started making my own maps.
fun game
I asked for it and they did it. .. i can now mute the game and listen to audiobooks  while playing. Awesome service!!
Addictive and great!
Good game!
Never had a crash yet with it. Pretty enjoyable I just wish there were different modes in random games. Gets a bit repetitive after a while. Feels a bit too simple.
Addictive, fun, engaging, excellent game.  Would be really nice to turn the sound off so I can listen to music at the same time.
I paid for the full version after only 3 practice games, I'm hooked. It's easy to play, fun and I'm hoping challenging at harder levels. Thanks devs.
It had me hooked for quite a while.
You can't go wrong here!
Lots of fun. Well worth the price of admission.
this could be good but gets too hard too quickly i find. plus the game seems to stop doing activities for no reason :-\

Not too bad, shame the Hard levels are so stacked against you, and the AI cheats with unlimited minerals! You have black hole, leave AI with one planet and they send infinite ships against you...built from what I have no idea? Make it a fairer fight and could be good game.
But prompt response to email from devs even though there's no fix for my device (wildfire) deserves 4 stars.

Good game overall. But there is a little glitch in scoring. On the last robot uprising level, I got beat real quick and scored over 1300 points and leveled up. When I did somewhat better and survived 170 days, I scored les than 200 points. So it looks like if I want to level up real quick I just need to go get my butt kicked a few times.
But could use multiplayer and volume options
Only suggestion is that we should be able to trade with another players and maybe add a real time multiplayer option?

Good time killer.  Ideas for updates: - home button loses all saved game status. Needs to be fixed. Nothing like getting into the game answering a text and having to start all over again. -planet changing from galaxy view to planets pauses production on the planets. Would be nice to have it continue building without manually pressing fast forward or play. I'm only in it for 10 minutes through the tutorial and freeplay but i noticed some bugs needing correction.  (Used to play ogame and eve)
Awesome game. Runs without trouble. Only change I wish is that you could build your own maps

Great little game. Polish and extra features, like being able to zoom out to take full advantage of fuel upgrades, are hopefully on their way. Level/experience rewards system is a novel yet good break from the norm, allowing you to add starting resources or extra tech levels.  Has a LOT of potential - keep your eye on this developer!
This is a good start. Add races, technologies, ship classes, diplomacy, resource, resource allocation, colonists, growth and make it MOO. On a tablet out will work.
Small, simple, and entertaining game. Experience bonus system is great for adding replayability. Would like option to custom generate my own maps though.
replyContent:
Hi, thanks for your comment:) There is a free tool for map generating available on our website. 
http://blueplop.com/star-colonies/game.html , the last paragraph at the bottom of the page. We made all levels with this. Then you can download maps to your SD Card.

content: Reminds me of Master of Orion
Really enjoy the game, but often I do not have the time to finish a level, and you cannot save in the middle of a game.  This alone keeps me from starting it up.

While quite simple, the game mechanics work very well. You still need your brain to go through the campaigns. It's getting a bit repetitive toward the end, but the fun before is definitely worth the price
Not yet Master of Orion and the game lack of features but closest to MOO Android game I found.
Must buy
This is a great game, but it is quite hard, be warned.

This game is great!  Looking forward to  a sequel. Hopefully you can add more races, custom ships and space battles?  I'm glad to see someone finally tackled this genre.  Master of Orion 2 and master of magic were two of the best games I ever played

ANDROID NEEDS MORE OF THIS GENRE!!! Good game with interesting and easy to get into User Interface! Has potential for more! A.I. is a bit predictive and can be trapped/manipulated. Bit of a battery hog (needs an in-game Battery meter display). Wish it has more reseach options, different shiptypes (light/ fast fighters, medium cruisers, slow/tanking battleships, orbital  defense stations) other than that, good game for the subways ;-)
Game is thought out and very well design. Like how you need to gain resources, research and tactical troops in this game. Great game, hopefully you add more aliens and different maps
Reminds me of alite version of Master of Orion
Want more maps please
Can't wait for a "extra large" universe option!
Simple to learn. Complex enough to play again and again.

Extremely good game, & the development team is the best! I can't recommend this game more
:)

I play this more than almost  anything else. The maps are hard enough to be frustrating if you set them up that way, but aren't impossible. It reminds me of a junior version of Sins of a Solar Empire. Someday I'll look into designing my own maps, but I enjoy the add-on maps offered on their website.
Only complaint is that normal and hard are like hard and fatal lol but great challenge!
The game itself is well designed and would be good if not for the horrendous AI making it practically impossible even on easy level settings.   Too bad... ruins the game.  Uninstalled.
It is a very well designed game. I would prefer a pinch to zoom instead of the toggle zoom, but it doesn't affect game play.

Great game. Better still if there are other ship type and ships can attack each other. Worth the money spent on buying full version.  Hope to see more games like this from DevTeam like sea battles maybe

Simplest 4x ever.  Nice but some buttons don't work right.  Interesting mechanics - extra power stations amplify shields, for instance.  Wish for smarter/more diverse ai and more possible combinations of buildings such as power generation in asteroids or outposts powering shields.
Awesome game. Very fun to play.
It has some quirks but it's worth the buy. Biggest complaint is you can't turn off the sounds. Also wish the in game alerts were less intrusive

Rapid and nonstop expansion is the only way to win (higher cost to colonize would increase strategy).  Also there's only one unit type, some of the icons aren't explained (what's the house next to the planet mean?) but this is still about the best in mobile 4X gaming.
Awesome

I love/hate this game, it's so addictive I look up and an hour's gone by or I've missed by stop on the tube! Very reminiscent of Master of Orion. It's a great simple game, I'd like to see a bit more complexity, for example more info about the different "races" and the ability to rename planets. The same old planet names each game gets quite repetitive. Also the tutorial isn't that great, it only gives the basic mechanics without explaining what all the icons mean!

I really like the game play, but it seems pretty buggy for a paid app.  The active research seems to show up on the row above, the game doesn't save when android closes the app (or when it loses focus), but expects the user to bavk out to the menus before switching tasks...  I don't think they play tested it much.   Hoping for a bugfix update soon.
Reminds me a little of "Master of Orion"... Very very good and challenging.
I love playing this. The only downside is that you receive more points for losing than you do for a win.
This game is very well-executed. The basic graphics and gameplay are offset by the low price. Very elegantly executed, and very addictive for a two-D game with minimal eye candy.
Outstanding
As a former Master of Orion addict, this game is quite entertaining.

First of all I love this game but some maps just seem way too hard even impossible.  I need help with battle times map 6 space garden.  Anyone know the trick to win?  Also cannot beat Robot Revenge, New Home map 6. Any help with that one would be great also.  I have beat every other map.
Great!
This brings me back to master of Orion.

I just beat all the campaigns (including the newest ones), it has the perfect level of challenge.  I experienced a few lockups on my TF-101, but I usually was able to save and return to continue playing.
This game has lots of potential, but can get repetitive. I'd like to see more options, more upgrades, and more technology.
Nice little game
It's a good game except every time my phone restarts so does my game, then I start all over
A little strange that you get more points for losing on hard than winning on any difficulty, but its a great little game. Needs a variety of ship types though.
This is a good game but most of the maps are impossible. You cannot do anything but get pounder by an endless stream of enemy ships. Makes half the maps unplayable.
Needs player vs player and more ship types. Other than that very awsome game!

This is a very playable, addictive and fun game. It's quite challenging without being impossible. Lots game play. Keeps your interest - the devs are active in improving the game. Be sure to check out the manual on the developer website.
Well worth the price of admission to kill a few hours.. music reminds of moo..  thanks devs.. hope we see more of this!
Awesome game can't wait for new levels or a way to play against other players
Liked.it so.much I bought the product . Look forward to the next.version.

Wow! From the first tutorial I loved this game, I can't believe how fun it is and how addicted I am! It is quite complex to begin with, then you develop strategies and understand it 100% ... why isn't this app number 1 yet? ... must spread the word!!!! Thanks!!!!!!!
Simple to play title that allows a novice to play and be successful and also Offers a simple tech tree for more advanced game play. definitely recommend for all strategy fans
I beat all the maps :(
Good game with lots of replay value. Additional upgrades larger systems and more opponents would be ideal but overall nice work.

I wish I could zoom in or out so I could see the whole map. That would make it easier to go from galaxy to galaxy and easier to see where my ships are coming from and going cuz its hard to keep track of everything when you have 10 + planets. And the ships should have some kind of line that shows were they came from and where there going. You should also make it show the progress of building ships and buildings next to the planets. Have different variety of ships for more strategy , great game but incomplete
It's challenging in just the right way.
Well wirth the download. tok me awhile but im level 30
Fun and runs well
Great RTS game. Gets the balance right between complex and fun.

Really entertaining as a quick space empire game, its comparison to master of Orion is deserved, also very similar to galactic civilisations. Room to expand though, I got full version to help plop do that ;) hint hint

Lots of fun. 20 minutes can get you through a random map and campaigns are more involved. Would love to see bigger research trees and obtaining experience to gain levels /points to spend is a little too difficult. Overall fun and well balanced.
Space is my 2nd favorite genre next to fantasy, and i really like build n conquer games!
Decent game for a phone has great potential for a great game
Good but kinda repetative
Great game play.  Simple design and controls yet it feels like a larger game.about half way through the tutorial missions and would already have paid$5 for it!
Fun game at a Buck fifty you wont be disappointed.
Cant even install, motorola defy

Reminds me of a game I played way back when on an Atari ST called Supremacy. That was great and so is this!  A tablet interface would really help when playing on my Xoom and game profile slots so my wife and I can play without waiting for each other to finish would be icing on the cake
Crashed way less now
You have to play this game.
Addictive but had some bugs that stop me playing . like not being able to re conquer a planet if lost.
Great game. A little deeper into weapon types or ships would be awesome. Maybe a bit more building focus as opposed to amassing starships would be fantastic. Highly recommend!
Quick and fun, a good time killer.
First class game, quick to master and challenging as you progress, if you like games like c&c and star craft you will like this one.
Fans of MoO will enjoy it for sure.

This is a well designed, fun to play game. It would be nice to have settings to turn off sound. larger galaxies, pinch to zoom, and ship/weapon types would make this a game of the year. Do that and it's 5 stars from me. As is it's just a good game that could be great. I hope you keep working on this one!
Please add tablet interface.
Good layout and well balanced between the AI and different raises. All in all a awesome game!!!
Well done.
Must have for MoO fans
Long term MoO fan, this makes for a really nice and hectic alternative!
The game is an excellent and challenging strategy. It would deserve five stars, however deleting game data in update did make me pretty unhappy..
